    "Pearson Correlation Coefficient (r) was used to determine the strength and direction of the relationship between the variables.",
    "All hypotheses were tested at 0.05 level of significance.",
    "Table 1a shows the distribution of students in terms of age.",
    "With a rate of 73.3 percent or thirty-three (33) from their total number, it reveals that most of the respondents are fifteen years old followed by sixteen and fourteen years old.",
